1 olive oil
2 clove garlic
½ Brown Onion
½ head cos lettuce
½ carrot
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet pork mince
1 packet oyster sauce
1 tbs soy sauce
8 Mini Flour Tortillas
½ fresh chilli  (optional)
1 radish
1 packet Crispy Shallots

• Finely chop garlic and onion (see ingredients).
• Shred cos lettuce (see ingredients). Grate the
carrot (see ingredients).

Little cooks: Don your goggles and have a go at
peeling off the onion's outer layer!

• In a small bowl, add garlic aioli and season with
salt and pepper. Stir to combine. Set aside.

Little cooks: Help prep the aioli!

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat. When oil is hot, add
onion and carrot, season with salt and cook,
stirring, until softened slightly, 4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.

• Increase heat to high, then add pork mince
and cook, breaking up with a spoon, until just
browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then add oyster sauce
and the soy sauce and stir until just combined,
1 minute. Season to taste.

• While the pork is cooking, microwave mini flour
tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts, until
warmed through.

• Thinly slice fresh chilli (if using) and radish.
Spread a thin layer of aioli over tortillas.
• Top with some cos lettuce and Vietnamese-style
pork and veggies.
• Sprinkle with crispy shallots, radish and chilli to
serve. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Take the lead and help build the tacos!
Enjoy!